Comment:
Strictly speaking we are still in the opening stage;
yet already White is experience some difficulty in maintaining the tension.
The root cause is the weakened diagonal e1-h4

Black's plan of entry into the
White position is threeforl: First ... Pf5, then ... Pb5 to open the b-file;
finally ... Pd5 breaking into the centre

Obviously White avoids
further liquidation. His one aim now is to keep the pieces on the board;
otherwise his attack would fizzle out
